docs.abstract: The transition from older, shrinking markets to new areas is proving difficult for tech’s most venerable companies. But that does not mean they won’t be able to reinvent themselves.
docs.snippet: The transition from older, shrinking markets to new areas is proving difficult for tech’s most venerable companies. But that does not mean they won’t be able to reinvent themselves.
docs.lead_paragraph: For the tech industry’s venerable giants, the new stuff just doesn’t seem to be worth as much as the old stuff.

headline.main: Daily Report: IBM Caught Between the Old and the New

headline.main: Morning Agenda:  A Growing Conflict in Wall St. Buyouts

docs.abstract: The overturning of a previous conviction in an insider trading case will test the S.E.C.’s efforts in two similar cases.
docs.snippet: The overturning of a previous conviction in an insider trading case will test the S.E.C.’s efforts in two similar cases.
docs.lead_paragraph: The government files insider trading charges with much fanfare, declaring that the traders will be brought to justice and investors protected. But it is often years before the cases ever reach a courtroom, and a change in the law in December 2014 is making it more difficult for the Securities and Exchange Commission to prove violations in two cases that will start in the new year.

headline.main: In Cohen and I.B.M. Insider Trading Cases, Challenges for the S.E.C.

docs.abstract: The computing giant’s new areas, such as data analytics, its Watson software and cloud computing, have yet to grow fast enough to supplant company’s eroding legacy products.
docs.snippet: The computing giant’s new areas, such as data analytics, its Watson software and cloud computing, have yet to grow fast enough to supplant company’s eroding legacy products.
docs.lead_paragraph: IBM delivered fresh evidence on Tuesday of the financial challenge it faces in navigating a difficult transition to new technology businesses. Yet the company’s leaders insisted its performance also showed that its strategy was succeeding.

headline.main: IBM Reports Declines in Fourth-Quarter Profit and Revenue Despite Gains in New Fields
headline.print_headline: IBM Reports Drop in Fourth-Quarter Profit Despite Gains in New Fields

docs.abstract: Mr. Sapper was especially revered by coffee connoisseurs for his lustrous stovetop Coban 9090 espresso maker, sold by Alessi, the Italian housewares manufacturer.
docs.snippet: Mr. Sapper was especially revered by coffee connoisseurs for his lustrous stovetop Coban 9090 espresso maker, sold by Alessi, the Italian housewares manufacturer.
docs.lead_paragraph: Richard Sapper, an industrial designer whose sleek, precision-engineered prototypes spawned the Alessi espresso maker, the Tizio lamp and the IBM ThinkPad, died on Dec. 31 in Milan. He was 83.

headline.main: Richard Sapper, Designer of Sleek Housewares, Dies at 83
headline.print_headline: Richard Sapper, 83, Maker of Classic Product Designs
